# XERO08 Export Error: Report PDF Is Too Large

If you see the error message **“XERO08 Export Error: PDF of report is too large to export (>10MB). Please reach out to Concierge for additional assistance.”**, it means the generated report PDF exceeds Xero’s 10MB attachment limit.

Xero does not allow attachments larger than 10MB.

---

## Why the XERO08 Export Error Happens

The XERO08 export error occurs when:

- The report PDF generated by Expensify is larger than **10MB**, and  
- Xero rejects the attachment during export  

Large PDFs are commonly caused by:

- High-resolution receipt images  
- A large number of attachments on a single report  
- Scanned documents with high file sizes  

---

## How to Fix the XERO08 Export Error

Please reach out to **Concierge** in Expensify for assistance.

On web:

1. Go to the **navigation tabs on the left**.
2. Select **Concierge**.
3. Start a new message and reference the **XERO08 Export Error**.

On mobile:

1. Tap the **navigation tabs on the bottom**.
2. Select **Concierge**.
3. Start a new message and reference the **XERO08 Export Error**.

Concierge will review the report and help determine the best way to successfully export it to Xero.

---

# FAQ

## Can I reduce the PDF size myself?

You may try removing unnecessary or duplicate attachments from the report and reattempting the export. If the error persists, contact Concierge.

## Does this error affect other reports?

Only reports with PDFs larger than 10MB will fail. Smaller reports will export normally.
